    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1964-04-06T07:45:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1964-04-06T07:45:00-05:00" n="12"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d12">
                <head>12. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Embassy in Iran</gloss> to the <gloss
                        type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d12fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, POL 23–9 IRAN. Confidential. Repeated to Baghdad and Karachi.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Tehran</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1964-04-06T16:15:00+03:30">April 6, 1964, 4:15 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>882. Ayatollah Khomeini, at first imprisoned and later under house detention in
                    connection 1963 Moharam riots and widely regarded as leading contender for
                    position of Shia paramount leader, was released April 5 and returned to
                    religious center of Qom. Press giving minimum play. [<hi rend="italic">less than
                        1 line of source text not declassified</hi>] reports (1) millahs flocking to
                    Qom from all over Iran to “kiss hands“, and (2) one tank battalion concentrated
                    Qom outskirts as precautionary measure. No info whether <persName
                        corresp="#p_KAR1">Khomeini</persName> reached agreement with govt regarding
                    any restriction on his future activities. Embassy [<hi rend="italic">less than 1
                        line of source text not declassified</hi>] contacts with good connections in
                    religious community view release as victory for <persName corresp="#p_KAR1"
                        >Khomeini</persName> but also as wise policy decision by regime in
                    preparation for Moharam, period of deep mourning starting May 13.</p>
                <p>Request Baghdad and Karachi report any clerical reaction <persName
                        corresp="#p_KAR1">Khomeini</persName>’s release.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="strong">
                            <persName corresp="#p_HJC2">Holmes</persName>
                        </hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
